'''“狗吃了我的作業”'''（{{lang-en|"The dog ate my homework" }}）是一種[[英語|英語]]表達方式，一般意指學童未能按時上交作業的一種常見的、拙劣的藉口，該短語在1970年代開始被廣泛引用<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.npr.org/2012/10/13/162845021/can-the-dog-still-eat-your-homework |title=Can The Dog Still Eat Your Homework? |author=Scott Simon and Forrest Wickman |date=October 13, 2012 |work=National Public Radio |accessdate=October 14, 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121014173705/http://www.npr.org/2012/10/13/162845021/can-the-dog-still-eat-your-homework |archive-date=October 14, 2012 }}</ref>，用來諷刺那些拙劣、難以相信的解釋。

